[3] Pakistan (Punjab)
Date: Thu 18 Jan 2018
Source: Geo News [edited]
https://www.geo.tv/latest/177446-influenza-outbreak-death-toll-in-multan-rises-to-24


A seasonal outbreak of influenza [Influenza A/H1N1] claimed another life in Multan on [Thu 18 Jan 2018], taking the death toll to 24. The deceased, a 22-year-old girl hailing from Layyah (District in Punjab Province), was under treatment at Nishtar Hospital (Multan), informed hospital officials.

The spokesperson for the Multan's health department remarked that 3 more influenza [Influenza A/H1N1] patients have been admitted to Nishtar Hospital in the last 24 hours. At least 197 patients have been admitted to the hospital in last month [December 2017], of which 103 were diagnosed with influenza [Influenza A/H1N1], the spokesperson shared, adding that the doctors are waiting for the reports of 8 patients.

Influenza [Influenza A/H1N1] has claimed 24 lives in Multan in the past month and 25 patients are currently under treatment at the hospital.

